{"word":"ἔγγυος","slug":"ἔγγυος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἔγγυος, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐν\">ἐν</a>, γυῖον</el> ‘limb (arm, leg, hand)’, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ἐγγύη</el> ‘pledge put into one’s hand’; the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> signifies ‘under good security’] in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> only as noun <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a> <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἔγγυος\">ἔγγυος</a></el> and as a legal metaphor ‘one who serves as surety’, <b>guarantor, surety <a href='B:650 7:22'>Hb 7:22</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐγγράφω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐγγύς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}